{"title_page": "IPhone SE (2020)", "text_new": "{{short description|Smartphone announced in 2020}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{in use}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name         = iPhone SE (2020)\n| codename     = \n| logo         = iPhone SE 2020.png\n| logosize     = <!-- include \"px\" - Uses users default image size if omitted -->\n| image        = IPhone_8_Product_Red_vector.svg\n| imagesize    = \n| alt          = \n| caption      = 2020 iPhone SE in Product Red\n| brand        = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| manufacturer = \n| slogan       = ''Lots to love. Less to spend.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/|title=iPhone SE|website=Apple|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415160521/https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/|archive-date=April 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| serieslabel  = [[History of iPhone|Generation]]\n| series       = 13th\n| modelnumber  = \n| networks     = \n| released     = {{Start date and age|2020|04|24}}\n| available    = <!-- Country {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} (Retailer) -->\n| discontinued = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| unitssold    = \n| unitsshipped = \n| predecessor  = [[iPhone SE (2016)]]<br>[[iPhone 8]]\n| successor    =  \n| related      = [[iPhone 11]]<br>[[iPhone 11 Pro]]\n| type         = [[Smartphone]]\n| form         = Slate\n| size         = {{convert|138.4|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<ref name=\"Official website: specifications>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/specs/|title=iPhone SE - Technical Specifications|website=Apple|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> {{convert|67.3|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /> <br /> {{convert|7.3|mm|in|abbr=on}} D<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| weight       = {{convert|148|g|oz|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| os           = [[iOS 13|iOS 13.41]]\n<!-- | '''Original:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n<!-- | '''Current:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n| soc          = [[Apple A13 Bionic]]<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| cpu          = \n| gpu          = \n| modem        = \n| memory       = \n| storage      = \n| memory_card  = \n| battery      = \n| charging     =\n| input        = \n| display      = {{convert|4.7|in|mm|abbr=on}} [[Retina display|Retina HD display]] with [[IPS panel|IPS]] technology, 1334 \u00d7 750 pixel resolution (326 [[pixels per inch|ppi]]), 1400:1 contrast ratio (typical)<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| ext_display  = \n| rear_camera  = 12MP, \u0192/1.8 aperture, optical image stabilization, Six-element lens, True Tone flash, autofocus, 4K video recording at 24 fps, 30 fps, or 60 fps or 1080p HD video recording at 30 fps or 60 fps or 720p HD video recording at 30 fps, Cinematic video stabilization (4K, 1080p, and 720p), Slo\u2011mo video support for 1080p at 120 fps or 240 fps, Time\u2011lapse video with stabilization, Portrait mode, Portrait lighting, and Smart HDR\n| front_camera = \n| sound        = \n| connectivity = \n| other        = \n| sar          = \n| hac          = \n| website      = {{URL|www.apple.com/iphone-se/}}\n| references   = \n}}\n{{iPhone models}}\nThe '''iPhone SE''' (officially '''second-generation iPhone SE''') is a [[smartphone]] designed and marketed by [[Apple Inc.]] It is part of the 13th generation of the iPhone alongside the [[iPhone 11]], [[IPhone 11 Pro|iPhone 11 Pro and Pro Max]]. Announced on April 15, 2020, the iPhone SE serves as a successor to both the [[iPhone SE (original)|2016 iPhone SE]] and the [[iPhone 8]]. Pre-orders will begin on April 17, 2020, and will be available on April 24, 2020.\n\n== History ==\nA successor to the [[iPhone SE]] has been rumored since 2017, just a year after the device was released.{{fact|date=April 2020}}\n\nThe phone also had two other rumored names: iPhone SE 2 and (more recently) iPhone 9, due to this phone sharing a design with the iPhone 8.\n\nIn March 2020, cases for the phone were reportedly being shipped to [[Best Buy]],<ref name=\"9to5mac\">{{Cite web|url=https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/|title=iPhone 9 case inventory arriving at Best Buy, other retailers with April 5 merchandising date|last=Miller|first=Chance|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403181051/https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/|archive-date=April 3, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> showing an iPhone with an [[iPhone 8]]-sized body, a single camera lens for the regular model.<ref name=\"9to5mac\" /> [[Belkin]] screen protectors for this phone had also being sold at [[Apple Store|Apple]], compatible with the regular-sized versions of the [[iPhone 8]] and [[iPhone 7]]. However, the ''iPhone SE'' branding was quickly removed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tomsguide.com/news/apple-iphone-9-will-be-the-new-iphone-se|title=iPhone 9 will be called iPhone SE and could launch soon (Update)|website=Tom's Guide|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"9to5mac\" />\n\n== Design ==\nThe iPhone SE features a design with an aluminum frame, and its front and back is made out of glass. The phone's external design and dimensions are nearly identical to that of the iPhone 8, with the exception of a centered Apple logo. It features bezels on the top and bottom of the front and a home button integrated with [[Touch ID]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/|title=iPhone SE 2020: Everything We Know|website=MacRumors|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805112853/https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/|archive-date=August 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe iPhone SE is available in three colors; White, Black, and Product Red.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Color Name !!Front\n|-\n|White||Black\n|-\n|Black ||Black\n|-\n|Product Red||Black\n|-\n|}\n\n== Specifications ==\n\n===Hardware===\nThe iPhone SE incorporates the [[Apple A13|Apple A13 Bionic system-on-chip]] (SoC) with an [[Apple A13|M13]] [[Apple motion coprocessors|motion coprocessor]]. It will be available in three internal storage configurations; 64 GB, 128 GB and 256 GB.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications2\" /> \n\n==== Display ====\nThe iPhone SE features the same Retina HD display found on the [[iPhone 8]].<ref name=\"Official website: specifications3\" /> However, [[Force Touch|3D Touch]] is replaced by Haptic Touch.\n\n==== Camera ====\nThe iPhone SE features a 12 MP rear camera similar to the wide camera of [[iPhone 11]] and [[iPhone 11 Pro]]. The camera has a \u0192/1.8 aperture, with autofocus, optical image stabilization, and a quad-LED True Tone flash. It is capable of recording 4K video at 24 fps, 30 fps, or 60 fps, 1080p HD video at 30 fps or 60 fps, or 720p HD video at 30 fps. The phone can also take panoramas up to 63 MP, and is capable of shooting photos in burst mode.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications4\" />\n\nThe front camera of the iPhone SE is a 7 MP camera with \u0192/2.2 aperture and autofocus, capable of shooting 1080p HD video at 30 fps.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications5\" />\n\nBoth the front and rear cameras of the iPhone SE support Smart HDR, Portrait mode and Portrait Lighting.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications6\" /> Unlike the iPhone 11 and 11 Pro, iPhone SE does not support Night mode.\n===Software===\nThe iPhone SE will ship with [[iOS 13]], which includes Apple Pay and supports Apple Card.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n== Timeline of iPhone models ==\n{{Timeline of iPhone models}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{iOS}}\n{{Apple hardware since 1998}}\n{{Apple Inc. hardware}}\n{{Apple}}\n\n[[Category:IPhone|*]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 2020]]\n[[Category:iOS]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2020]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Smartphone announced in 2020}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{in use}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name         = iPhone SE (2020)\n| codename     = \n| logo         = iPhone SE 2020.png\n| logosize     = <!-- include \"px\" - Uses users default image size if omitted -->\n| image        = IPhone_8_Product_Red_vector.svg\n| imagesize    = \n| alt          = \n| caption      = 2020 iPhone SE in Product Red\n| brand        = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| manufacturer = \n| slogan       = ''Lots to love. Less to spend.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/|title=iPhone SE|website=Apple|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415160521/https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/|archive-date=April 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| serieslabel  = [[History of iPhone|Generation]]\n| series       = 13th\n| modelnumber  = \n| networks     = \n| released     = {{Start date and age|2020|04|24}}\n| available    = <!-- Country {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} (Retailer) -->\n| discontinued = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| unitssold    = \n| unitsshipped = \n| predecessor  = [[iPhone SE (2016)]]<br>[[iPhone 8]]\n| successor    =  \n| related      = [[iPhone 11]]<br>[[iPhone 11 Pro]]\n| type         = [[Smartphone]]\n| form         = Slate\n| size         = {{convert|138.4|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<ref name=\"Official website: specifications>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/specs/|title=iPhone SE - Technical Specifications|website=Apple|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> {{convert|67.3|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<ref name=\"Official website: specifications /> <br /> {{convert|7.3|mm|in|abbr=on}} D<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| weight       = {{convert|148|g|oz|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| os           = [[iOS 13|iOS 13.41]]\n<!-- | '''Original:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n<!-- | '''Current:''' For use ONLY after new release -->\n| soc          = [[Apple A13 Bionic]]<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| cpu          = \n| gpu          = \n| modem        = \n| memory       = \n| storage      = \n| memory_card  = \n| battery      = \n| charging     =\n| input        = \n| display      = {{convert|4.7|in|mm|abbr=on}} [[Retina display|Retina HD display]] with [[IPS panel|IPS]] technology, 1334 \u00d7 750 pixel resolution (326 [[pixels per inch|ppi]]), 1400:1 contrast ratio (typical)<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| ext_display  = \n| rear_camera  = 12MP, \u0192/1.8 aperture, optical image stabilization, Six-element lens, True Tone flash, autofocus, 4K video recording at 24 fps, 30 fps, or 60 fps or 1080p HD video recording at 30 fps or 60 fps or 720p HD video recording at 30 fps, Cinematic video stabilization (4K, 1080p, and 720p), Slo\u2011mo video support for 1080p at 120 fps or 240 fps, Time\u2011lapse video with stabilization, Portrait mode, Portrait lighting, and Smart HDR\n| front_camera = \n| sound        = \n| connectivity = \n| other        = \n| sar          = \n| hac          = \n| website      = {{URL|www.apple.com/iphone-se/}}\n| references   = \n}}\n{{iPhone models}}\nThe '''iPhone SE''' (officially '''second-generation iPhone SE''') is a [[smartphone]] designed and marketed by [[Apple Inc.]] It is part of the 13th generation of the iPhone alongside the [[iPhone 11]], [[IPhone 11 Pro|iPhone 11 Pro and Pro Max]]. Announced on April 15, 2020, the iPhone SE serves as a successor to both the [[iPhone SE (original)|2016 iPhone SE]] and the [[iPhone 8]]. Pre-orders will begin on April 17, 2020, and will be available on April 24, 2020.\n\n== History ==\nA successor to the [[iPhone SE]] has been rumored since 2017, just a year after the device was released.{{fact|date=April 2020}}\n\nThe phone also had two other rumored names: iPhone SE 2 and (more recently) iPhone 9, due to this phone sharing a design with the iPhone 8.\n\nIn March 2020, cases for the phone had reportedly being shipped to [[Best Buy]],<ref name=\"9to5mac\">{{Cite web|url=https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/|title=iPhone 9 case inventory arriving at Best Buy, other retailers with April 5 merchandising date|last=Miller|first=Chance|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403181051/https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/|archive-date=April 3, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> showing an iPhone with an [[iPhone 8]]-sized body, a single camera lens for the regular model.<ref name=\"9to5mac\" /> [[Belkin]] screen protectors for this phone had also being sold at [[Apple Store|Apple]], compatible with the regular-sized versions of the [[iPhone 8]] and [[iPhone 7]]. However, the ''iPhone SE'' branding was quickly removed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tomsguide.com/news/apple-iphone-9-will-be-the-new-iphone-se|title=iPhone 9 will be called iPhone SE and could launch soon (Update)|website=Tom's Guide|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"9to5mac\" />\n\n== Design ==\nThe iPhone SE features a design with an aluminum frame, and its front and back is made out of glass. The phone's external design and dimensions are nearly identical to that of the iPhone 8, with the exception of a centered Apple logo. It features bezels on the top and bottom of the front and a home button integrated with [[Touch ID]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/|title=iPhone SE 2020: Everything We Know|website=MacRumors|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805112853/https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/|archive-date=August 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe iPhone SE is available in three colors; White, Black, and Product Red.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Color Name !!Front\n|-\n|White||Black\n|-\n|Black ||Black\n|-\n|Product Red||Black\n|-\n|}\n\n== Specifications ==\n\n===Hardware===\nThe iPhone SE incorporates the [[Apple A13|Apple A13 Bionic system-on-chip]] (SoC) with an [[Apple A13|M13]] [[Apple motion coprocessors|motion coprocessor]]. It will be available in three internal storage configurations; 64 GB, 128 GB and 256 GB.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications2\" /> \n\n==== Display ====\nThe iPhone SE features the same Retina HD display found on the [[iPhone 8]].<ref name=\"Official website: specifications3\" /> However, [[Force Touch|3D Touch]] is replaced by Haptic Touch.\n\n==== Camera ====\nThe iPhone SE features a 12 MP rear camera similar to the wide camera of [[iPhone 11]] and [[iPhone 11 Pro]]. The camera has a \u0192/1.8 aperture, with autofocus, optical image stabilization, and a quad-LED True Tone flash. It is capable of recording 4K video at 24 fps, 30 fps, or 60 fps, 1080p HD video at 30 fps or 60 fps, or 720p HD video at 30 fps. The phone can also take panoramas up to 63 MP, and is capable of shooting photos in burst mode.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications4\" />\n\nThe front camera of the iPhone SE is a 7 MP camera with \u0192/2.2 aperture and autofocus, capable of shooting 1080p HD video at 30 fps.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications5\" />\n\nBoth the front and rear cameras of the iPhone SE support Smart HDR, Portrait mode and Portrait Lighting.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications6\" /> Unlike the iPhone 11 and 11 Pro, iPhone SE does not support Night mode.\n===Software===\nThe iPhone SE will ship with [[iOS 13]], which includes Apple Pay and supports Apple Card.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n== Timeline of iPhone models ==\n{{Timeline of iPhone models}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{iOS}}\n{{Apple hardware since 1998}}\n{{Apple Inc. hardware}}\n{{Apple}}\n\n[[Category:IPhone|*]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 2020]]\n[[Category:iOS]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2020